                "accelerator"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The reaction ejectiles were momentum analyzed",
                "with an Enge split- pole magnetic spectrograph"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH",
                "DRFTC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "The tritons were focused at the",
                "spectrograph's focal plane, where they were detected",
                "with an isobutane-filled position sensitive",
                "ionization drift chamber. The ionization chamber",
                "measured the positions along the focal plane and energy",
                "losses dE of the tritons."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Tritons that passed through ionization chamber",
                "deposited their residual energy in the plastic",
                "scintillator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The dE, E, and position (proportional to",
                "momentum) were measured to identify tritons and",
                "determine their momenta. The tritons were selected",
                "according to dE and Eres, which were plotted vs focal",
                "plane position gates. The spectra of the tritons",
                "momenta were then plotted for each spectrograph",
                "angle. Triton peaks corresponding to 30S states in",
                "these spectra were clearly identified through",
                "kinematic analysis."
              ]
            }
          ],
